<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-16T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/10: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-16T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 16,
                                            1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your despatch No. 2720 of May 9.</p>
                            <p>Department does not consider that you should undertake to extend
                                protection to nationals of non-treaty countries unless requested by
                                those Governments, consented to by China and authorized by
                                Department.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>